<node CREATED="1206359786015" ID="Freemind_Link_1926379726" MODIFIED="1206359798812" TEXT="what is the function here?"/>
</node>
<node CREATED="1206359839890" ID="Freemind_Link_1961356101" MODIFIED="1206359840953" TEXT="So-called &quot;active&quot; systems simulate a GSM base station and don&apos;t rely on encryption because they trick phones into connecting to the GSM network through them. "/>
<node CREATED="1206359875265" ID="Freemind_Link_761819939" MODIFIED="1206359876359" TEXT="Hutton and Steve&apos;s technology relies on the use of an array of devices known as field programmable gate arrays to first create a table of all the possible encryption keys -- in this case 288 quadrillion -- and then decrypt each of those over the course of three months. The resulting tables of keys could then be used by software to decrypt GSM communications, which first have to be intercepted using a receiver that can listen in on GSM frequencies."/>
</node>
<node CREATED="1206358875187" FOLDED="true" ID="Freemind_Link_869806799" LINK="http://www.gcn.com/online/vol1_no1/45852-1.html" MODIFIED="1206367657484" TEXT="GCN">
