<node CREATED="1206367090093" FOLDED="true" ID="Freemind_Link_817743888" MODIFIED="1206394359906" TEXT="comment and reaction">
<node CREATED="1206358603750" ID="Freemind_Link_156060693" MODIFIED="1206358605109" TEXT="that their cheaper technique is simply drawing needed attention to a problem that mobile carriers have long ignored"/>
<node CREATED="1206358645265" ID="Freemind_Link_1288556377" MODIFIED="1206358647468" TEXT="&quot;This is a nice piece of work, but it isn&apos;t a surprise,&quot; he says. &quot; We&apos;ve been saying that this algorithm is weak for years. The mobile industry kept arguing that the attack was just theoretical. Well, now it&apos;s practical.&quot;"/>
<node CREATED="1206359696062" ID="Freemind_Link_279412067" MODIFIED="1206359697156" TEXT="greatly decrease the time and money required to decrypt, and therefore snoop on, phone and text message conversations taking place on GSM networks."/>
<node CREATED="1206358603750" ID="Freemind_Link_1581175506" MODIFIED="1206358605109" TEXT="that their cheaper technique is simply drawing needed attention to a problem that mobile carriers have long ignored"/>
<node CREATED="1206366799796" ID="Freemind_Link_1675921516" MODIFIED="1206366799796" TEXT="David Pringle, a spokesperson for the GSM Association (GSMA),">
<node CREATED="1206356428578" ID="Freemind_Link_540801088" MODIFIED="1206366818593" TEXT="declined to comment on the specifics of the duo&apos;s research, saying engineers there hadn&apos;t had time to review it. But he defended the security and resiliency of the A5/1 privacy algorithm, saying the attacks detailed to date have been more theoretical than practical."/>
</node>
</node>
